#: ../../versioning.rst:30
msgid ""
"A big part of Vyper's \"public API\" is the language grammar. The syntax "
"of the language is the main touchpoint all parties have with Vyper, so "
"it's important to discuss changes to the language from the viewpoint of "
"dependability. Users expect that all contracts written in an earlier "
"version of Vyper will work seamlessly with later versions, or that they "
"will be reasonably informed when this isn't possible. The Vyper package "
"itself and its CLI utilities also has a fairly well-defined public API, "
"which consists of the available features in Vyper's `exported package "
"<https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/blob/master/vyper/__init__.py>`_, the"
" top level modules under the package, and all CLI scripts."
msgstr "Vyper 的“公共 API”的很大一部分是语言语法。语言的语法是所有各方与 Vyper 的主要接触点，因此从可靠性的角度讨论语言的更改非常重要。用户希望所有用早期版本的 Vyper 编写的合约都能与更高版本无缝协作，或者在无法实现时能得到合理的通知。Vyper 包本身及其 CLI 实用程序也有一个定义相当明确的公共 API，它由 Vyper 的 `导出包 <https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/blob/master/vyper/__init__.py>`_ 中的可用功能、包下的顶级模块以及所有 CLI 脚本组成。"

#: ../../versioning.rst:41
msgid "Version Types"
msgstr "版本类型"

#: ../../versioning.rst:43
msgid ""
"This guide was adapted from `semantic versioning <https://semver.org/>`_." 
" It defines a format for version numbers that looks like "
"``MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH[-STAGE.DEVNUM]``. We will periodically release "
"updates according to this format, with the release decided via the "
"following guidelines."
msgstr "本指南改编自 `语义版本控制 <https://semver.org/>`_。它定义了一种版本号格式，看起来像 ``MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH[-STAGE.DEVNUM]``。我们将根据此格式定期发布更新，发布将根据以下准则决定。"

#: ../../versioning.rst:49
msgid "Major Release ``X.0.0``"
msgstr "主要版本 ``X.0.0``"

#: ../../versioning.rst:51
msgid ""
"Changes to the grammar cannot be made in a backwards incompatible way "
"without changing Major versions (e.g. ``v1.x`` -> ``v2.x``). It is to be "
"expected that breaking changes to many features will occur when updating "
"to a new Major release, primarily for Developers that use Vyper to "
"compile their contracts. Major releases will have an audit performed "
"prior to release (e.g. ``x.0.0`` releases) and all ``moderate`` or "
"``severe`` vulnerabilities will be addressed that are reported in the "
"audit report. ``minor`` or ``informational`` vulnerabilities *should* be "
"addressed as well, although this may be left up to the maintainers of "
"Vyper to decide."
msgstr "在不更改主要版本（例如 ``v1.x`` -> ``v2.x``）的情况下，不能以向后不兼容的方式更改语法。可以预见，在更新到新的主要版本时，许多功能都会发生重大更改，这主要针对使用 Vyper 编译其合约的开发人员。主要版本将在发布前进行审计（例如 ``x.0.0`` 版本），并且审计报告中报告的所有 ``中等`` 或 ``严重`` 漏洞都将得到解决。``次要`` 或 ``信息性`` 漏洞也*应该*得到解决，尽管这可能由 Vyper 的维护者决定。"

