#: ../../versioning.rst:110
msgid "Vyper Security"
msgstr "Vyper 安全"

#: ../../versioning.rst:112
msgid ""
"As Vyper develops, it is very likely that we will encounter "
"inconsistencies in how certain language features can be used, and "
"software bugs in the code the compiler generates. Some of them may be "
"quite serious, and can render a user's compiled contract vulnerable to "
"exploitation for financial gain. As we become aware of these "
"vulnerabilities, we will work according to our `security policy "
"<https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/security/policy>`_ to resolve these "
"issues, and eventually will publish the details of all reported "
"vulnerabilities `here "
"<https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/security/advisories?state=published>`_." 
" Fixes for these issues will also be noted in the :ref:`Release Notes"
"<release-notes>`."
msgstr "随着 Vyper 的发展，我们很可能会遇到某些语言功能使用方式的不一致，以及编译器生成的代码中的软件错误。其中一些可能非常严重，并可能使用户编译的合约容易受到以获取经济利益为目的的利用。当我们意识到这些漏洞时，我们将根据我们的 `安全策略 <https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/security/policy>`_ 来解决这些问题，并最终将 `在此处 <https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/security/advisories?state=published>`_ 发布所有报告的漏洞的详细信息。这些问题的修复也将在 :ref:`发行说明<release-notes>` 中注明。"

#: ../../versioning.rst:123
msgid "Vyper *Next*"
msgstr "Vyper *Next*"

#: ../../versioning.rst:125
msgid ""
"There may be multiple Major versions in the process of development. Work "
"on new features that break compatibility with the existing grammar can be"
" maintained on a separate branch called ``next`` and represents the next "
"Major release of Vyper (provided in an unaudited state without Release "
"Notes). The work on the current branch will remain on the ``master`` "
"branch with periodic new releases using the process as mentioned above."
msgstr "开发过程中可能有多个主要版本。破坏与现有语法兼容性的新功能的工作可以在一个名为 ``next`` 的单独分支上进行维护，它代表 Vyper 的下一个主要版本（在未经审计的状态下提供，没有发行说明）。当前分支的工作将保留在 ``master`` 分支上，并使用上述过程定期发布新版本。"

#: ../../versioning.rst:132
msgid ""
"Any other branches of work outside of what is being tracked via "
"``master`` will use the ``-alpha.[release #]`` (Alpha) to denote WIP "
"updates, and ``-beta.[release #]`` (Beta) to describe work that is "
"eventually intended for release. ``-rc.[release #]`` (Release Candidate) "
"will only be used to denote candidate builds prior to a Major release. An"
" audit will be solicited for ``-rc.1`` builds, and subsequent releases "
"*may* incorporate feedback during the audit. The last Release Candidate "
"will become the next Major release, and will be made available alongside "
"the full audit report summarizing the findings."
msgstr "``master`` 跟踪之外的任何其他工作分支将使用 ``-alpha.[release #]`` (Alpha) 来表示 WIP 更新，并使用 ``-beta.[release #]`` (Beta) 来描述最终打算发布的工作。``-rc.[release #]`` (Release Candidate) 将仅用于表示主要版本之前的候选版本。将为 ``-rc.1`` 版本征求审计，后续版本*可以*在审计期间采纳反馈。最后一个候选版本将成为下一个主要版本，并将与总结调查结果的完整审计报告一起提供。"

#: ../../versioning.rst:142
msgid "Pull Requests"
msgstr "拉取请求"

#: ../../versioning.rst:144
msgid ""
"Pull Requests can be opened against either ``master`` or ``next`` branch,"
" depending on their content. Changes that would increment a Minor or "
"Patch release should target ``master``, whereas changes to syntax (as "
"detailed above) should be opened against ``next``. The ``next`` branch "
"will be periodically rebased against the ``master`` branch to pull in "
"changes made that were added to the latest supported version of Vyper."
msgstr "可以针对 ``master`` 或 ``next`` 分支打开拉取请求，具体取决于其内容。将增加次要版本或补丁版本的更改应针对 ``master``，而对语法的更改（如上所述）应针对 ``next`` 打开。``next`` 分支将定期针对 ``master`` 分支进行变基，以拉入添加到最新支持的 Vyper 版本中的更改。"

#: ../../versioning.rst:151
msgid "Communication"
msgstr "沟通"

#: ../../versioning.rst:153
msgid ""
"Major and Minor versions should be communicated on appropriate "
"communications channels to end users, and Patch updates will usually not "
"be discussed, unless there is a relevant reason to do so."
msgstr "主要版本和次要版本应通过适当的沟通渠道向最终用户进行沟通，而补丁更新通常不会被讨论，除非有相关的理由这样做。"